message.content: The smallest integer that is greater than or equal to $\frac54$ is $2$, so $\left\lceil{\frac54}\right\rceil = 2$. The largest integer that is less than or equal to $-\frac54$ is $-2$, so $\left\lfloor{-\frac54}\right\rfloor = -2$. Therefore, $\left\lceil{\frac54}\right\rceil+\left\lfloor{-\frac54}\right\rfloor = 2 + (-2) = \boxed{0}.$
